….As BVAS Fails to accredit Wike, wife By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) – The presidential candidate of New Nigeria Peoples Party (NNPP), Senator Rabiu Kwankwaso has casted his ballot at a polling station in Kano. This is also as the Bimodal Voters Accreditation System (BVAS) failed to accredit Governor of Rivers State, Nyesom Wike and his wife in Rivers. Sundiata Post recalls that Nigerians are today electing the president, Muhammadu Buhari and the federal lawmakers in the red and green Chambers. Details later……